  "title": "Tragedy or Triumph: An Improvised Shakespearean Epic",
  "description": "The award winning Spontaneous Shakespeare Company return to Edmonton. Come see a once-in-a-lifetime Shakespearian epic, based off of your story! Will it be a heart rending tragedy or an epic romance? Not even the cast knows! \"...a delightful celebration of what improv — and Shakespeare — can be.\" ★★★★★ - Star Phoenix",
  "credits": "<strong>Playwright</strong>: The Spontaneous Shakespeare Company<br/><strong>Director</strong>: Brent Hirose<br/><strong>Cast</strong>: Trista Peterson, Nikolai Witschl, Zach Wolfman, Abdullah Wasfi, Indu Iyer, Caitlin Maira, Julia Lank<br/>",
  "website": "https://spontaneousshakespeare.com",
  "plain_language": "This show begins by taking an everyday story from an audience member. The improvisers will then turn this story into a Shakespeare-style play. The audience gets to choose if it is a tragedy or a romance. Past shows have included many of Shakespeare's tropes. This includes murders, plots, mistaken identity and magic. Every show is different, but all will be funny and dramatic. No Shakespeare knowledge is required.",
